      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for the paper **\"Measuring Causal Effects of Data Statistics on Language Model's 'Factual' Predictions\"** (arXiv: 2207.14251):\n\n**Authors:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Yanai Elazar, Nora Kassner, Shauli Ravfogel, Amir Feder, Abhilasha Ravichander, Marius Mosbach, Yonatan Belinkov, Hinrich Schütze, and Yoav Goldberg."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Published:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Published on July 28, 2022 on arXiv (arxiv:2207.14251)."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Summary:**\n\nThe paper asks a key question: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\"what exactly in the training data causes a model to make a certain prediction?\""
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors seek to answer this by providing a language for describing how training data influences predictions, through a causal framework."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Importantly, the framework bypasses the need to retrain expensive models and allows estimating causal effects based on observational data alone."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Addressing the problem of extracting factual knowledge from pretrained language models (PLMs), they focus on simple data statistics such as co-occurrence counts and show that these statistics do influence the predictions of PLMs, suggesting that such models rely on shallow heuristics."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Key links:**\n- **arXiv page:** https://arxiv.org/abs/2207.14251\n- **PDF:** https://arxiv.org/pdf/2207.14251\n- **Semantic Scholar:** https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Measuring-Causal-Effects-of-Data-Statistics-on-Elazar-Kassner/f92d5dcc04b2f7713befce4e84e3084bfd4abd50"
      }
    ],
